# Multi-Tool Sync Contract

## Canonical Source of Truth

The `.cursor/` directory is the SINGLE canonical source. All other tool
directories are GENERATED MIRRORS. Never edit mirrors directly.

### Tier 1 — Fully Maintained (complete parity, actively tested)

| Mirror directory   | Target tool            | Sync method         |
|--------------------|------------------------|---------------------|
| `.antigravity/`    | Antigravity IDE        | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `.codex/`          | Codex app / Codex CLI  | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `.claude/`         | Claude Code / CLI      | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `AGENTS.md`        | Codex CLI (root)       | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `CLAUDE.md`        | Claude Code (root)     | `pnpm ai:sync`      |

### Tier 2 — Best-Effort (synced but not actively tested; may lag by 1-2 minor versions)

| Mirror directory   | Target tool            | Sync method         |
|--------------------|------------------------|---------------------|
| `.kilocode/`       | Kilo IDE               | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `.opencode/`       | OpenCode               | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `.windsurf/`       | Windsurf IDE           | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `.roo/`            | Roo Code               | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `.qwen/`           | Qwen CLI               | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `.gemini/`         | Gemini CLI             | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `GEMINI.md`        | Gemini CLI (root)      | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `QWEN.md`          | Qwen CLI (root)        | `pnpm ai:sync`      |
| `WINDSURF.md`      | Windsurf IDE (root)    | `pnpm ai:sync`      |

> **Universal fallback:** Any tool that reads `CLAUDE.md` or `AGENTS.md` at repo root
> can use NEZAM. The canonical slash commands and SDD pipeline work regardless of tool.

## Automated Sync (Git Hook)

A pre-commit hook auto-runs `pnpm ai:sync` whenever `.cursor/` files are staged.
This prevents mirror drift from being committed accidentally.

**Install the hook (run once after cloning):**
```bash
bash scripts/setup-hooks.sh
```

**Hook source:** `scripts/hooks/pre-commit` (tracked in repo)
**Hook destination:** `.git/hooks/pre-commit` (not tracked — local only)
**Skip for one commit:** `git commit --no-verify`

The hook:
1. Detects if any `.cursor/` files are staged
2. Runs `pnpm ai:sync`
3. Re-stages generated mirror files (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, .claude/, etc.)
4. Fails the commit if sync errors out

## Sync Rules (enforced)

1. After ANY edit to `.cursor/commands/`, `.cursor/agents/`, `.cursor/skills/`,
   or `.cursor/rules/` — run `pnpm ai:sync` before committing.
2. CI runs `pnpm ai:check` on every PR. Drift fails the build.
3. Root-level `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `GEMINI.md` are GENERATED from
   `.cursor/` — they contain the command/agent/skill/rule index only.
4. If a tool reads its own mirror (e.g., Claude reads `CLAUDE.md`) it MUST
   follow the rules defined in `.cursor/rules/workspace-orchestration.mdc`.
5. All tools share identical SDD pipeline order, hardlock rules, and
   gate matrix — divergence is a bug.

