## Session Handoff Protocol

When switching tools mid-session:
1. Run `/SAVE log` in the current tool to persist session state.
2. The next tool reads `docs/nezam/memory/MEMORY.md` on boot.
3. Run `/GUIDE status` in the new tool to confirm sync before continuing.

## Mirror Sync Content Policy

Each mirror directory receives exactly:
- Commands → from `.cursor/commands/`
- Agents   → from `.cursor/agents/`
- Skills   → from `.cursor/skills/`
- Rules    → from `.cursor/rules/`

Root-level contract files (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md) receive:
- Auto-generated index of synced commands, agents, skills, rules
- Required behavior block from workspace-orchestration.mdc
- Tool-specific session start protocol from this file

## Drift severity scale

Use **`pnpm ai:status`** (`node scripts/sync-ai-folders.js --status`) for a quick mirror survey. Severity guides whether to block work or only warn:

| Severity | Signal | Handling |
|----------|--------|----------|
| **CRITICAL** | Any mirrored **`.mdc` rule body** differs from canonical `.cursor/rules/` — especially **`workspace-orchestration.mdc`**, **`sdd-pipeline-v2.mdc`**, hardlock gates, or design-gate contracts | Treat as **blocking**: do not rely on routed commands until `pnpm ai:sync`; re-run `/START all` or `/GUIDE status` after sync |
| **WARNING** | **Agent/command markdown** differs (non-identical synced copies under `.claude/`, `.codex/`, `.opencode/`, etc.) | Surface warning; workflows may proceed for local-only work; **avoid** parallel-tool execution until synced |
| **INFO** | Whitespace/markdown wrapping only — no semantic change (`pnpm ai:sync` is idempotent noop except formatting) | Run `pnpm ai:sync` on next touch to `.cursor/`; no user-facing blocker |

Canonical definition of drift remains **`pnpm ai:check`** in CI (`scripts/sync-ai-folders.js` drift + integrity scripts).
